        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 17 at 6:06PM MDT until August 17 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Phillips County in northeastern Montana...
Petroleum County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 700 PM MDT.

* At 605 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 14 miles east of Winifred to 16 miles south of Grass
Range, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Observed gusts of around 60 mph in Fergus county.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Winnett, Flatwillow, Petrolia Lake, Fred Robinson Bridge,
Valentine, Cat Creek, and Tiegen.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
